        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 6:31PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 631 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms over northeastern Weld County, or 30 to 40 miles
northwest of Sterling, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Westplains and Pawnee Buttes.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Prepare for sudden gusty winds. Secure loose objects and move to a
safe shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
